Returns:

RenewToken()[source]

This function checks if the access token has expired or not. If it has we create a new oauth session We also refresh if the token is valid for less than one day

Returns:

this function does not return anything

Request(url: str, query: str)[source]

This functions sends a request to the WCL API

Parameters:

  • url – full URL of the request

  • query – This is what we want to request from WCL

Returns:

It returns the response from the WCL API for the query we gave it

RequestEvent(log_code: str, data_type: str, fight_id: str)[source]

This function sends the selected event request to the WCL API

Parameters:

  • log_code – the code of the log we want the API to read

  • data_type – type of the event we want to scrape,

https://www.warcraftlogs.com/v2-api-docs/warcraft/eventdatatype.doc.html <- for future possibility to expand the cog methods :param fight_id: the fight encounters we want to analyze the data from :return: returns the response from the WCL API for the event query we gave it

RequestGuild(guild_name: str, serv_name: str, server_reg: str)[source]

This function sends the guild request to the WCL API

Parameters:

  • guild_name – name of the guild whose members we want to check

  • serv_name – name of the server of the guild

  • server_reg – region of the guild server

Returns:

It returns the response from the WCL API for the guild query we gave it
